columns.name: VACANT ON 12/31
columns.description: "YES -  the storefront was reported vacant on 12/31 of the reporting year. NO - the storefront was reported owner-occupied or leased on 12/31 of the reporting year."

columns.name: CONSTRUCTION REPORTED
columns.description: YES - construction is reported in the storefront as of 12/31.

columns.name: VACANT 6/30 OR DATE SOLD IF EARLIER
columns.description: "For Classes 2 and 4: YES -  following 12/31 of the reporting year, the storefront was reported vacant on 6/30 or the date the property was sold if earlier than 6/30.  Blank means there is no reported information.     "

columns.name: PRIMARY BUSINESS ACTIVITY
columns.description: "For Classes 2 and 4: Local Law 157 requires owners to submit a supplemental registration to report any property ownership changes or storefronts that become vacant between 1/1 and 6/30 after the reporting year, and for the Department of Finance to identify storefronts reported vacant as of 6/30.  Some property owners who did not submit main registrations or submitted main registrations with missing information used the supplemental registration to provide information on the vacancy status of storefronts for both 12/31 and 6/30.    For Class 1: Registered class 1 storefronts were not required to update their status as of 6/30 or date sold if earlier than 6/30.  "

view.description:
Storefronts Reported Vacant or Not. The dataset was created to comply with Local Law 157 of 2019. Data is collected using an online portal, which allows owners to provide information about ground and second floor storefronts on their properties.

Each row shows a ground floor or second floor storefront that was registered with the department as of December 31 of the reporting year and legally required updates provided as of June 30 (or date sold if earlier) of the calendar year immediately following the reporting year. Each row contains the property's borough, block and lot number and the storefront's street address (and zip code), either field can be used to search for individual storefronts.
